<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-155-074  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 155 074.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Hewlett-Packard Journal  Feb 1990 v41 n1 p92(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Linewidth and power spectral measurements of single-frequencylasers. (Hewlett-Packard's 11980A Fiber Optic Interferometer)(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Baney, Douglas M.; Sorin, Wayne V.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hewlett-Packard's 11980A Fiber Optic Interferometer is intended towork with the company's 71400A Lightwave Signal Analyzer tomeasure important spectral modulation properties ofsingle-frequency telecommunication lasers.andP;  The device convertsoptical phase or frequency deviations into intensity variationsthat can be detected using a square-law photodetector, such as thehigh-speed photodiode of the 71400A.andP;  An unbalanced fiber opticMach-Zehnder interferometer in the 11980A has an input directionalcoupler that splits the incoming optical signal into two equalparts that travel along separate fiber paths, being recombinedafter a differential delay.andP;  Both the 74100A and the 11980A havethe same adaptable fiber optic connectors compatible with theHMS-10/HP, FC/PC, ST, biconic and DIN connector formats.andP;  Laserdiode linewidth, measuring linewidth and modulated laser powerspectrum measurement are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hewlett-Packard Co. (products).andO;Ticker:    HWP.andO;Product:   HP 11980A Fiber Optic Interferometer (Test equipment, electronic)(design and construction).andO;Topic:     LasersMeasurementSignal ProcessingTest EquipmentOptical CommunicationsFiber OpticsFrequency Modulation.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartgraph.andO;Caption:   Distributed feedback laser linewidth measurement: delayedself-homodyne. (chart)Linewidth measurement for a DFB laser operating at 1,549nanometers. (graph)Two-sided measurement of the same laser linewidth. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>